<h2>The question</h2>
<p>
  Prep research for decision
  <a href="/backlog/513-train-quantize-the-distilled-verdict-classifier-10mb-onnx-st/">#513</a> — a
  <strong>go/no-go training-readiness gate</strong>, not a design fork. All five
  <a href="/backlog/488-on-device-ui-screenshot-vision-model-as-a-plateau-capability/">#488</a> design
  forks are already ratified in
  <a href="/backlog/490-build-the-on-device-verdict-classifier-codified-distillation/">#490</a>'s codified
  spec (≤10MB MobileNet/ViT student, ONNX Runtime Web + WebGPU runtime, task-specific KD recipe in
  <a href="/backlog/511-design-ref-corpus-export-codified-distillation-recipe-artifa/">#511</a>, the
  ≥0.95 verdict-agreement / ≥0.98 quarantine-recall graduation floors in
  <a href="/backlog/512-on-device-verdict-benchmark-harness-verdict-agreement-quaran/">#512</a>). The
  student architecture and KD method are <em>empirical model-selection the #512 benchmark auto-decides</em>
  — not a human-judgment fork. The single forced question:
</p>
<blockquote>
  Is the design-ref corpus large + balanced enough to distil a ≤10MB student that clears the #512 floors
  on the 6-verdict taxonomy yet?
</blockquote>
<p>
  Grounded count: <code>design-refs/items/</code> holds <strong>16</strong> captures,
  <code>design-refs/quarantine/</code> holds <strong>0</strong> — but
  <code>design-refs/training-manifest.json</code> reports <code>total:0</code> /
  <code>unlabeled:16</code>: <strong>every shot is ungated</strong> (no vision provider has run over the
  corpus), so there are <strong>zero labeled training examples and zero labeled holdout</strong>. The #512
  floors are not even <em>measurable</em> today.
</p>
<p>
  Prior art grounds the threshold. The task-specific KD methods named in #490's recipe
  (<a href="https://openaccess.thecvf.com/content/CVPR2025/papers/Jang_VL2Lite_Task-Specific_Knowledge_Distillation_from_Large_Vision-Language_Models_to_Lightweight_CVPR_2025_paper.pdf">VL2Lite</a>,
  <a href="https://arxiv.org/html/2408.16930v1">VLM-KD</a>, and the dual-head
  <a href="https://arxiv.org/html/2505.07675">DHO</a> line) report their low-data regime as
  <strong>K-shot × C-class, N = K×C</strong>, with <strong>16-shot</strong> the empirical low-data
  sweet-spot (DHO across 11 datasets; the broader few-shot literature puts the cost-effective knee in the
  10–16-shot range, and notes adding <em>classes</em> helps more than adding samples per class). For a
  <strong>6-class</strong> taxonomy that floors a usable distillation set at
  <strong>N ≈ 16 × 6 ≈ 96 labeled captures</strong>, balanced ~16 per verdict.
</p>

<h2>Recommendation (to ratify in #513)</h2>
<p>
  <strong>WAIT</strong> — the proceed-now branch is broken below the corpus floor. Distilling from
  <strong>0</strong> labeled captures cannot clear the #512 floors, so there is nothing to ratify yet. This
  is a single <strong>forced invariant</strong>, not a fork: there is no legitimate competing end-state
  ("proceed now on 0 labeled shots" is not a coherent branch, it just fails the benchmark).
</p>
<p>
  <strong>Un-block trigger (grounded, numeric).</strong> Once
  <code>design-refs.mjs collect</code>/<code>harvest</code> has run a real vision provider so the manifest
  reports:
</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>≥~96 labeled captures total</strong> (the N = 16×6 low-data floor), <em>and</em></li>
  <li><strong>≥16 labeled examples in EACH of the four quarantine classes</strong> (marketing / error /
    blank / non-app) — this is the <em>binding</em> constraint, because the ≥0.98 quarantine-recall floor
    rides on the rare tail, not the common <code>app</code> class, <em>and</em></li>
  <li>a <strong>non-empty labeled holdout split</strong> (<code>holdoutFraction 0.15</code>) — required
    just to <em>score</em> the gate.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  …the proceed branch goes live: the mechanical #511 recipe runs and the #512 benchmark decides the
  student. At that point #513 retypes to a <code>story</code> and is resolved by building.
</p>
<p>
  <strong>Skeptic.</strong> Could a smaller corpus proceed? For the easy <code>app</code> ↔
  <code>non-app</code> split, plausibly — but the real bar is the <strong>0.98 quarantine-recall on the
  rare tail</strong>, and a sub-16-per-quarantine-class corpus cannot reliably clear a 0.98 recall floor
  (you cannot estimate, let alone hit, 0.98 recall from a handful of positives). The threshold
  <strong>SURVIVES</strong>.
</p>

